0.body: This repository contains the code for the Micro Core Library, this project defined Assertion, File wrapper, math types definitions and functions, platform's specific wrapper function, Multi-threading work management and Yaml file support.
0.title: MicroCore

1.body: MicroCore as part of the Micro project use the Premake5 build system. Premake5 instance is present in this repository under Build/Premake5. Build files for Premake5 are inside Build folder under : File Usage Build/Build.lua Define global solution build. Build/Build-MicroCore.lua Define MicroCore solution build. Build/Build-Thirdparty.lua Define Thirdparty solution build.
1.title: Build System

caution To use the logger you need to created it before any micro::log call. // Create logger.
micro::create_log( "LOG", "xxxx.log" ); // Log with information log level.
micro::log_info( "Thread id : {0}", std::thread::get_id( ) ); // Log with trace log level.
micro::log_trace( "Thread id : {0}", std::thread::get_id( ) ); // Log with warning log level.
micro::log_warn( "Thread id : {0}", std::thread::get_id( ) ); // Log with error log level.
micro::log_errr( "Thread id : {0}", std::thread::get_id( ) );

176.body: This section of the documentation present thread work management and emission. Work manager create and manage is threads internaly with the ability to push work to be executed by it's threads. Work Work Manager You can also find examples for the class usage. Example
176.title: Work Management

177.body: This section cover work creation for usage by the work manager. Work are based on callbacks function that are executed in order when the work manager process-it. Callbacks Work also define a priority flag. Priorities All member functions of the class are defined in the list bellow : Constructor Constructor<T> GetIsValid Operator The template constructor also fil work cache data, maximum cache data is 64 bytes aka 16 float matrix, to ensure data can be store in the cache, the constructor use requirement concept . Requirements You can also find examples for the class usage. Example

186.body: Name Description MWP_HIGH When this priority is used, the work is push to high priority queue and process before low priorities work. MWP_LOW When this priority is used, the work is push to low priority queue and process after high priorities work.

187.body: tip When a work with High priority is pushed to the manager, is execution is always made before any low priority work regardless of pushing order.

To enable MICRO_DEBUG you need to define it before your include of the library. #define MICRO_DEBUG
